<br>
I fear I am destined to be a barmaid forever. How can this be?? I am a high elf, for mercy's sake! Not a sullied barmaid! This is the work of those not so ... tall... as me. Perhaps this is a lesson from the Goddess herself, that I must humble myself. It is a difficult lesson, but one I am willing to undertake, I suppose, if I must. <br>
<br>
I find myself not missing the guild hall so much these days. Rarely do I even wonder what is said there. I so enjoy my time divided between the Note and the Garden. I regret that my time has been limited between the two, that I've much to do. The wedding is to be soon, I must confess my excitement, to be wed to Darkmask. Never did I dare dream that love could be so grand. I swear, he is the very air I breathe. My heart pounds like the hooves of the centaurs across the plains of South Karana for him.<br>
<br>
Kesryn seems to have resolved himself to his memory loss. I do not know what to do for him, and I am confused as to his relations with Ani are. I believe she cares for him, but it appears that he is frightened of her at the same time. It is a most curious thing. Beltane almost chewed on his leg, I could swear I saw her eyeing him as if he were to be tomorrow's lunch. Naughty gnomes. <br>
<br>
Dorraxx is wonderful. Perhaps he would be a better bartender than myself, and a likely choice, as he knows his ales and brews far better than myself. I may be able to brew a good Gypsy Wine, or even Vodka, but, when it comes to telling them apart, I am not so wise. Definately a job for one shorter than myself. Besides, Dorraxx is good people, I could see many a folk spending a night over his bar, telling tales of sorrow. Ahh, which reminds me, I must tell Dorraxx what I am most curious about tomorrow, or when next I see him, should I remember.<br>
<br>
Surefoot has me a bit concerned. I hope he finds a balm for his heart. It seems he torments himself, desiring... I'm not sure what he desires, really, and I'm not sure he himself knows either.<br>
<br>
I grow weary. So tired. I hope I have not been gone so long that the bed has grown cold, lest I have to call on Darkmask to come and warm it for me......</i><br>
